                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10079: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-16T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Your 297, September 15, 3 p.m., from Harrison. Please in your discretion
                    inform Hoo that the American Government will make no decision regarding fact or
                    method of its possible cooperation with the League in regard to the
                    Japanese-Chinese situation unless and until approached by the League with some
                    concrete proposal formulated by the League.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
